Uses of Package
com.kuka.med.robotstate

  • Classes in com.kuka.med.robotstate used by com.kuka.med.robotstate 
    Class and Description
    EFailedConditionForNormalUse
    The possible causes why the robot is not ready for normal use.
    ETileState
    The possible state of a tile, i.e. system components as displayed on the smartHMI, and of each layer of its error message tree.
    ETriggerName
    Enumeration of all kinds of system events, that can trigger a RobotStateEvent.
    IErrorMsgTree
    The IErrorMsgTree interface provides the structure of messages as displayed on the smartPAD, i.e. text and state.
    IRobotStateEvent
    The RobotStateEvent provides information about the current state of the system and whether the pre-conditions for normal use are fulfilled.
    IRobotStateListener
    Interface, which is used to inform about state changes of the robot.
    ITileInfo
    The ITileInfo interface provides the relevant information about the system components which are represented as tiles in the smartHMI view on the smartPAD.
